{
  "stem": "18470.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And I said, may I interview you for a few minutes, because I write for Dewy Junior High School's newspaper.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she gave me an interview on education, which had that wonderful line that the first thing we need to do is re-educate the teachers, which article made me very popular with my teachers at Dewey Junior High.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] As a matter of fact, my English teacher called me in to ask me whether this was a correct quote.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I said, that's what she said.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[LAUGHTER] And then the next sentence is, why did you have to write it, you know, kind of thing.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I said, well, that's what she said.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "She-- that's what she thought the process had to begin.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So I had-- I had a very interesting time at junior high school.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "There was a teacher of geography by the name of Friedman, who took an inordinate interest, and I became great at geography.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And then Boys High School, my football coach was also chairman of the English and Spanish department, just a wonderful man with whom I corresponded until the year of his death.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "He was 90 years old, Wally Muller.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when my father died, I was in Boys High in 1946.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And the team became my family.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And it was a great experience.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "My high school experience pulled everything together for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Because both the fellows I was with and the teachers were challenging.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was an academic-- one of two academic high schools in the city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So the Americanization somehow, because my language facility was good, my athletic was-- facilities-- abilities were more than acceptable, and I got along with people.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And became a Hebrew teacher, which was the most difficult thing I ever did in my life.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why was it difficult?",
      "word_count": 4
    }
  ],
